observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE: (a) instruct the MA and the Disbursing Officers to: 

(1) submit to COA the required attachments to the CAs and corresponding liquidation reports both amounting to ₱12.23 million such as the approved payrolls, DTRs and Applications for leave, including the un-attached payrolls amounting to ₱394,862; 

(2) require the concerned employees to acknowledge the receipt of salaries amounting to ₱256,112 if indeed they received the payments; (3) to revise/re-arrange the documentation of various payrolls; and (b) require concerned personnel to comply strictly with Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445 and Sections 1.1.1, 1.2.1, 5.1 and 5.2 of COA Circular 2012-001.

We recommended that the LCE:
create an Inventory Committee that will conduct physical count of PPE, prepare the RPCPPE and submit the original copy to the Auditor;
direct the MAO to reconcile the results of inventory with the PPE accounts using the RPCPPE as basis and to verify and adjust/correct immediately any discrepancies noted;
direct the Property Unit to reconcile the results of inventory with the property records including Acknowledgement Receipts of Equipment and Inventory Custodian Slips issued to end users using the RPCPPE as basis and to verify and adjust/correct immediately any discrepancies noted;
require the MAO and the Property Unit to maintain the PPELC and PC, respectively, for all PPE; and
require all concerned personnel to ensure strict compliance with COA Circular No. 2020-006, Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGU, Volume 1, and Sections 13 and 45, Chapters I and II of the Manual on the NGAS for LGU Vol. II.

We recommended that the LCE:
instruct the MA and the DO to:
submit to COA the required attachments to the CAs and corresponding liquidation reports both amounting to ₱12.23 million such as the approved payrolls, DTRs and Applications for leave, including the un-attached payrolls amounting to ₱394,862 as cited in Number 3 above;
require the concerned employees to acknowledge the receipt of salaries amounting to ₱256,112 as cited in Number 4 above, if indeed they received the payments;
to revise/re-arrange the documentation of various payrolls as cited in Number 5 above; and
require concerned personnel to comply strictly with Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445 and Sections 1.1.1, 1.2.1, 5.1 and 5.2 of COA Circular 2012-001.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:

The Municipal Engineer to submit justification/s for the delay in project completion particularly of the two projects which were delayed by more than 200 days;

MA to compute accurately the liquidated damages based on the guidelines in item 8.1 of Annex E of the IRR of RA 9184.

We recommended that:

the Municipal Treasurer submits to Accounting Office all the disbursements vouchers, official receipts including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the  fifth day of the ensuing month;

the MA strictly complies with the timetable on the submission of accounts as required under existing laws, rules and regulations.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:

•	Municipal Engineer to submit justification/s for the delay in project completion particularly of the two projects which were delayed by more than 200 days;

•	Municipal Accountant to compute accurately the liquidated damages based on the guidelines in item 8.1 of Annex E of the IRR of RA 9184.

We recommended that:

the Municipal Treasurer submits to Accounting Office all the disbursements vouchers, official receipts including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the  fifth day of the ensuing month;

the Municipal Accountant strictly complies with the timetable on the submission of accounts as required under existing laws, rules and regulations.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:
Municipal Engineer to submit justification/s for the delay in project completion particularly of the two projects which were delayed by more than 200 days;
Municipal Accountant to compute accurately the liquidated damages based on the guidelines in item 8.1 of Annex E of the IRR of RA 9184.
